<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910618-0152</DOCNO><DOCID>910618-0152.</DOCID><HL>   Canadian Bond Offering</HL><DATE>06/18/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10</SO><IN>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)STOCK AND BOND REGISTRATIONS, PRICINGS (REG)</IN><NS>BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)BOND AND STOCK REGISTRATIONS AND PRICINGS (REG)</NS><RE>CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)</RE><LP>   OTTAWA -- The Canadian government said it will offer 1.7billion Canadian dollars (US$1.49 billion) of noncallablebonds in four issues this week.   The sale will involve 9.25% bonds due Dec. 15, 1994; 9.25%bonds due Oct. 1, 1996; 9.75% bonds due Dec. 1, 2001; and9.75% bonds due June 1, 2021. Offering terms will beannounced today.</LP><TEXT>   The Bank of Canada has agreed to purchase at least C$100million of the bonds.   Proceeds of the issue will be used to redeem C$1.70billion of Canadian government bonds maturing July 1.</TEXT></DOC>